                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>late 18th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይበል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>በእ፡ for በእንተ፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>እማ፡ for እማሬ፡</item>
                           <item>ካዕ፡ for ካዕበ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor, reigning King,
                           Patriarch and other persons; groups of lines in the incipit pages of
                           Texts I, III-3; incipits of all other texts and their sections; musical
                           notation signs; abbreviated directives for the ministers; some words,
                           e.g. ካዕበ, እንዘ, ወእምዝ, ጸሎት; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic
                           numerals and their elements.</seg>
                        <note>The handwriting remains fairly uniform
                           throughout the Ms. and is characterized by finely shape, slender and rather
                           upright letters. Occasionally it becomes notably right-sloping (e.g., <locus from="78v" to="86r">78v-86r</locus>).</note>
                     </handNote>
                     
                  </handDesc>
